    "summary": "I have worked in the industry since 1980 in various countries, both onshore and offshore, as follows : Brunei, Gabon, Netherlands, UK, Nigeria, Russia, Oman, Ireland and Iraq. During my 35+ years of career I have worked primarily in project management, with 4 years overall in broadening positions in both Finance and the M&A business. I am a well rounded professional with hands on experience in many varying situations.\n\nI have started up 3 oil major fields and 3 major gas fields, 5 under my accountabiilty as manager. I was responsible for the first ever safety case accepted by the UK HSE post. During my period in Nigeria in the 1990's I have stood at the birth of Social Performance in our industry. Recently I have been active in OD, Standards and IM/IT applications to improve the competitiveness of doing projects.\n\nI plan to retire from Shell (voluntarily !!!) on the 1st March 2016 and intend to take some time off until at least October 2016. I may be interested, at some stage, to do ad hoc consultancy work world wide.",
